An '''effective date''' or '''as of date''' is the [[Calendar date|date]] upon which something is considered to take effect, which may be a past, present or future date.  This may be different from the date upon which the event occurs or is recorded.<ref>{{citation |title=A taxonomy of time databases |pages=236–246 |year=1985 |ISBN=0-89791-160-1 |author=Richard Snodgrass|author-link=Richard T. Snodgrass}}</ref><ref>{{citation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=n7-jxMskU9MC&pg=PA6 |title=A manual of style for contract drafting |author=Kenneth A. Adams |isbn= 978-1-59031-380-0|year=2004}}</ref>

In Reserve Fund Planning, an effective date refers to the fiscal year's first day where changes, voted on at a condo or strata corporation [[Annual General Meeting]], take effect regardless of whether the vote took place before or after the beginning of the [[fiscal year]]. This effective date is when recommendations take place.

