{{Infobox language |name=Kol |states=[[Cameroon]] |speakers=12,000 |date=1988 |ref = <!--don't update to e18. it's the same figure, probably just citing Ethn. itself or Ethn's source-->e17 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone A|Zone A]]) |fam5=[[Makaa–Njem languages|Makaa–Njem]] + Kako (A.80–90) |fam6=Ndzem–Bomwali |fam7=Makaa |iso3=biw |glotto=kolc1235 |glottorefname=Kol (Cameroon) |guthrie=A.832 }}
'''Kol''' is a [[Niger–Congo languages|Niger–Congo language]] of the [[Bantu languages|Bantu]] family. It is spoken in the [[East Province (Cameroon)|East Province]] of [[Cameroon]], in the vicinity of [[Messaména]]. Alternate names for Kol language include Bikele-Bikay, Bikele-Bikeng, Bekol.
