{{BLP sources|date=July 2010}} '''Lobat Vala''' (born 1930 in [[Tehran]]) is an [[Iran]]ian [[poet]],<ref name="poetry-iranianwomen">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1eqE788O1WgC&pg=PP4&lpg=PP4&dq=%22Lobat+Vala%22+-facebook+-wiki+-photos&source=bl&ots=LJTJ13Wr13&sig=Z8jP8DjtpcTYHb3gnxDtY7FB2ww&hl=en&ei=FDAzTK7vIOPgsAa93anOBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=36&ved=0CI8BEOgBMCM#v=onepage&q=%22Lobat%20Vala%22%20-facebook%20-wiki%20-photos&f=false|title=The Poetry of Iranian Women|first=Sheema|last=Kalbasi|isbn=1-4421-0709-X}}</ref><ref name="netnative">{{cite news|url=http://www.payvand.com/news/08/oct/1082.html|title=Literature event with five Iranian exile authors in Vienna|date=2008-10-09|accessdate=2010-07-06|publisher=NetNative}}</ref> and campaigner for the Women Liberation and [[Women's rights|Equal Rights]] in Iran.<ref name="cecil-news">{{cite news|title=Campaigning for Freedom in Iran|page=5|url=http://www.emaconsult.co.uk/UserFiles/File/Cecil-CentralNewsWinter09.pdf|accessdate=2010-07-06|date=December 2009|newspaper=Central News: Newsletter for service users & supporters|publisher=Central & Cecil Housing Care Support}}</ref> Having been exiled from Iran since 1979, Vala lives in [[London]],<ref name="netnative"/> and lived in [[Melbourne]] between 1980 and 1984.{{Citation needed|date=July 2010}} While there she obtained an [[Master of Arts|MA]] in [[Middle Eastern Studies]] from [[University of Melbourne]] and in London worked as a [[journalist]] and writer in Keyhan weekly newspaper until 2006. {{Citation needed|date=July 2010}} Vala has published several poetry books in [[Persian language|Persian]].<ref name="netnative"/>
